  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2022.08.3-alpha-defbddf8`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: \r\n```\r\nDebian GNU/Linux 11\r\nLinux 5.10.0-15-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 5.10.120-1 (2022-06-09) x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n```\r\n\r\nCommit hash : `defbddf8d64718c71ec24c408f31c7f28ecf3e9e`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nUsing these flags to start a clean node:\r\n```\r\n--snapshots true --prune hrtc --prune.r.before=11184524 --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws --nat any --metrics --healthcheck\r\n```\r\nExpected to finish the initial sync\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nerigon goes into seemingly infinite loop at step 12: `StorageHistoryIndex` goes to ~15M and then wraps around back to beginning. No process restarts\r\n\r\nWraparound moment:\r\n```\r\nSep  2 16:59:44 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|16:59:44.213] [txpool] stat                            block=15399575 pending=9641 baseFee=0 queued=30000 alloc=6.0GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 16:59:44 eth systemd[1]: Starting Cleanup of Temporary Directories...\r\nSep  2 16:59:44 eth systemd[1]: systemd-tmpfiles-clean.service: Succeeded.\r\nSep  2 16:59:44 eth systemd[1]: Finished Cleanup of Temporary Directories.\r\nSep  2 16:59:54 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|16:59:54.514] [12/16 StorageHistoryIndex] Progress     number=14428816 alloc=3.6GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:00:22 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:00:22.431] Flushed buffer file                      name=/data3/etl-temp/erigon-sortable-buf-322213038 alloc=5.0GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:00:24 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:00:24.951] [12/16 StorageHistoryIndex] Progress     number=14435737 alloc=5.2GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:00:41 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:00:41.756] [p2p] GoodPeers                          eth66=108\r\nSep  2 17:00:44 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:00:44.248] [txpool] stat                            block=15399575 pending=9641 baseFee=0 queued=30000 alloc=3.9GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:01:04 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:01:04.082] Flushed buffer file                      name=/data3/etl-temp/erigon-sortable-buf-1730095966 alloc=5.0GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:01:04 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:01:04.228] [12/16 StorageHistoryIndex] etl: temp files removed total size=103.1GB\r\nSep  2 17:01:04 eth erigon[893]: [EROR] [09-02|17:01:04.229] Staged Sync                              err=\"[12/16 StorageHistoryIndex] error writing entries to disk: write /data3/etl-temp/erigon-sortable-buf-1730095966: no space left on d\r\nevice\"\r\nSep  2 17:01:38 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:01:38.433] [12/16 StorageHistoryIndex] Progress     number=2270493 alloc=4.7GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:01:44 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:01:44.220] [txpool] stat                            block=15399575 pending=9641 baseFee=0 queued=30000 alloc=5.2GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:02:07 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:02:07.448] Flushed buffer file                      name=/data3/etl-temp/erigon-sortable-buf-3392431681 alloc=3.9GB sys=12.5GB\r\nSep  2 17:02:09 eth erigon[893]: [INFO] [09-02|17:02:09.641] [12/16 StorageHistoryIndex] Progress     number=3446648 alloc=4.2GB sys=12.5GB\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nStart a clean node with `--snapshots true --prune hrtc --prune.r.before=11184524 --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws --nat any --metrics --healthcheck`\r\n\r\n",
